<<<api>>>: StringTokenizer.nextToken
<<<code>>>: Double dob1, dob2;
String str = "12345,56789";
StringTokenizer st = new StringTokenizer(str, ",");
dob1 = Double.parseDouble(st.nextToken());
dob2 = Double.parseDouble(st.nextToken());
System.out.println("dob1 = " + dob1);
System.out.println("dob2 = " + dob2);
<<<explanation>>>: In this code, we first create two Double variables dob1 and dob2. Then, we create a StringTokenizer object st and pass the string "12345,56789" and the delimiter "," to it. We use the nextToken() method to retrieve the next token from the StringTokenizer, which in this case is the first number "12345". We then use the Double.parseDouble() method to convert this string into a double and assign it to dob1. We repeat the same process for the second number "56789" and assign it to dob2. Finally, we print the values of dob1 and dob2.
